column5: Does anyone know for sure if the dock is in place at the boat ramp on the west end of the Chemong Lake causeway ??  I may fish there tomorrow if the dock is in but will go somewhere else if not. It's a great ramp with good parking but can be a pain by yourself without the dock to tie up to while parking the truck.
Just invite someone along, then you won't have to worry.
Great idea Albert, meet me at the ramp at 8 and bring your musky pole
Where's Adam when you need him ???
I haven't been over there Lew, but I've never seen it still not in at this point in the season.  S.
I could consider it, however I have a job interview tomorrow. Raincheck?
You available tomorrow Shane, I'll probably fish till early afternoon. .   Absolutely Albert, anytime at all.
Dutch Marina on the east side just north of the causeway, is a public launch as well, and is good with parking on the side of the road.
Thanks Steve, I know about that one but just prefer the causeway ramp but will be a back-up if need be, or maybe even run up to Emerald Ilse.
